          <h2 style="
              font-size: 20px;
              line-height: 1.2;
              font-weight: 500;
              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">ABC News defamation suit</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/ps-dec-16-1.jpg" alt="ABC News defamation suit" href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">ABC News has <a href="https://apnews.com/article/abc-trump-lawsuit-defamation-stephanopoulos-04aea8663310af39ae2a85f4c1a56d68" target="_blank">agreed</a> to pay $15 million to contribute to Donald Trump’s presidential library, resolving a defamation lawsuit filed by Trump over comments made by anchor George Stephanopoulos. During a segment in March 2024, Stephanopoulos wrongly stated that Trump had been found civilly liable for rape in writer E. Jean Carroll’s <a href="https://abcnews.go.com/US/jury-deliberations-underway-jean-carroll-battery-defamation-case/story?id=99183870" target="_blank">lawsuits</a>.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The settlement includes a $15 million contribution to a non-profit associated with Trump’s library and $1 million in legal fees for Trump’s attorney. ABC has issued a public apology and removed the incorrect statement. The settlement money should be transferred within 10 days to an escrow account managed by a British law firm, along with the legal fees. Earlier this year, the federal judges <a href="https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/abc-news-defamation-settlement-george-stephanopoulos-b2664857.html" target="_blank">rejected</a> ABC News’s arguments that Stephanopoulos’s statements were ‘substantially fair’ and protected under ‘fair report privilege.’</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
